This game is so much fun, but boring and irritating at the same time. You'll go through the levels in this game very fast... You could easily best it in a few hours or so. My biggest problem with this game is two things... Controls and the time / achievement (gold/silver/bronze) feature. The controls are very uneven, that is to say that your speed and acceleration when you move the goo stays the same - regardless if your a small tiny dot on the screen, or you've grown so large your almost half the size of the screen. When your small, that's an issue because your size is difficult to maneuver and try to pick up stuff, the speed is so fast in comparison to your size you'll find yourself backtracking across the screen-- and that hampers your time score, which i GUARANTEE you'll NEVER MAKE. I honestly don't know why the Gold/Silver/bronze ranking is even there, it doesn't change the outcome of the game nor does it add any content. And because of the aforementioned control issues when you are trying to move around as the goo on each level, its nearly IMPOSSIBLE to make said rankings. If you just play this as a time waster and don't care about a challenge or a time rank - this game is just fine for what it is.  It is legitimately fun eating everything as the goo and watching him progress and grow bigger and bigger.  The music is a little repetitive , and at times out of place in some levels ( jazzy music feels weird playing in what is basically Feudal Japan, and also going into Space and through the Solar System ...)
